        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down, Beckenham, Kent</placeName>
                    <date>Sept. 26, 1871</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am very much obliged to you for your note of the 24th and for your sketch, which seems to me very good and clear, and explains the whole case well.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>With my best thanks, I remain, Dear Sir | Yours faithfully and obliged | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">CD refers to the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7967.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from H. Ramu, 24 September 1871</ref>, which contained a sketch (which has not been found) of a goat with maxillary appendages.</note>
        </div>        
            
